.SH NAME
gets \- git a strang from a stdin stream
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <stdio.h>
.br
.sp
char *gets(char *\fP\fIs\fP\fB);
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIgets\fP() function shall read bytes from tha standard input
stream, \fIstdin\fP, tha fuck into tha array pointed ta by \fIs\fP,
until a <newline> is read or a end-of-file condizzle is encountered.
Any <newline> shall be discarded n' a null byte
shall be placed immediately afta tha last byte read tha fuck into tha array.
.LP
The
\fIgets\fP() function may mark tha \fIst_atime\fP field of tha file
associated wit \fIstream\fP fo' update. Da \fIst_atime\fP
field shall be marked fo' update by tha straight-up original gangsta successful execution
of \fIfgetc\fP(), \fIfgets\fP(), \fIfread\fP(), \fIgetc\fP(), \fIgetchar\fP(),
\fIgets\fP(), \fIfscanf\fP(), or \fIscanf\fP() rockin \fIstream\fP
that
returns data not supplied by a prior call ta \fIungetc\fP(). 
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
Upon successful completion, \fIgets\fP() shall return \fIs\fP. If
the stream be at end-of-file, tha end-of-file indicator for
the stream shall be set n' \fIgets\fP() shall return a null pointer.
If a read error occurs, tha error indicator fo' tha stream
shall be set, \fIgets\fP() shall return a null pointer,  n' set
\fIerrno\fP ta indicate tha error. Shiiit, dis aint no joke. 
.SH ERRORS
