.LP
Since tha user cannot specify tha length of tha buffer passed ta \fIgets\fP(),
use of dis function is discouraged. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da length
of tha strang read is unlimited. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! This type'a shiznit happens all tha time. Well shiiiit, it is possible ta overflow dis buffer
in such a way as ta cause applications ta fail, or possible
system securitizzle violations.
.LP
It be recommended dat tha \fIfgets\fP() function should be used to
read input lines.
